@startuml mesmerize-smart-3legged-oauth-athena
title Mesmerize SMART on FHIR — 3-Legged OAuth / Authorization Code Grant\nEHR launch from Athena (MVP) — ADR-005\nNo separate Mesmerize login for SMART app

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor "Clinician / Nurse / MA" as User
participant "Athena EHR\n(chart / encounter)" as Athena
participant "SMART App browser\n(React + fhirclient.js)" as SMART
participant "Athena\nAuthorization Server" as AuthZ
participant "Athena\nFHIR R4 API" as FHIR
participant "Mesmerize Platform API\n(session / content / devices)" as API

== 1. EHR launch (only MVP entry) ==
User -> Athena : Opens patient chart / encounter\nand launches Mesmerize
Athena -> SMART : Redirect / iframe to launch URL\niss + launch parameters\n(HTTPS https://smart…/launch)

note right of SMART
  **EHR launch only** (no standalone launch for MVP).
  App needs authenticated **provider** +
  **patient/encounter** context → **3-legged**
  Authorization Code Grant (not 2-legged).
end note

== 2. Authorization Code Grant (3-legged) ==
SMART -> AuthZ : Authorize request\nresponse_type=code\nclient_id=mesmerize-content-evidence\nscope=launch/encounter\n  patient/Patient.read\n  patient/Condition.read\n  patient/Encounter.read\n  patient/DocumentReference.write\nredirect_uri=…/callback\n(aud / state / PKCE as required)
AuthZ -> User : EHR SSO session already established\n(user consents / continues in EHR context)
AuthZ -> SMART : Redirect to /callback?code=…&state=…
SMART -> AuthZ : Token request\ngrant_type=authorization_code\ncode + client auth (private_key_jwt)
AuthZ -> SMART : access_token (+ id_token / refresh as issued)\nFHIR base URL / patient / encounter context

note over SMART
  **FHIR access_token stays in the browser only**
  Never sent to Mesmerize Platform API (ADR-002).
end note

== 3. Browser-side FHIR (EHR token) ==
SMART -> FHIR : GET Patient, Condition, Encounter\nAuthorization: Bearer <EHR access_token>
FHIR -> SMART : Patient display name,\nICD-10 Conditions, Encounter

== 4. Mesmerize session (separate token — no Mesmerize login UI) ==
SMART -> API : POST /api/sessions\nICD-10 codes + deviceGroupId only\n(+ tenantId/org context as applicable)\n**No** patient id / MRN / encounter id
API -> SMART : opaque sessionId +\nMesmerize session token

note over API
  Backend is zero-PHI:
  receives ICD-10 + device group + session id.
  Clinician did **not** sign into Mesmerize
  separately — Auth0 is for Command Center only.
end note

== 5. Later writeback (same EHR token, still browser-side) ==
SMART -> FHIR : POST DocumentReference\n(after physician approve; if enabled)\nAuthorization: Bearer <EHR access_token>
FHIR -> SMART : 201 Created

legend right
  |= Step |= Mechanism |
  | Launch | Athena EHR launch (iframe) |
  | Auth | 3-legged OAuth / Authorization Code Grant |
  | SSO | Athena / EHR SSO (no Mesmerize login) |
  | FHIR | Browser ↔ Athena FHIR |
  | Platform | Separate Mesmerize session token |
endlegend

@enduml
